      • resolve

        String resolve(XMLName tagName)
        Uses the manifest information to map an MXML tag to a ActionScript classname.
        Parameters:
        tagName - An XMLName representing an MXML tag, such as an <s:Button> tag.
        Returns:
        A fully-qualified ActionScript classname, such as "spark.controls.Button"

      • isLookupOnly

        boolean isLookupOnly(XMLName tagName)
        Determines if a manifest entry is "lookupOnly" or not.
        Parameters:
        tagName - An XMLName representing an MXML tag.
        Returns:
        true if tag name's manifest entry has its lookupOnly property set to true, and false otherwise.

      • getTagNamesForClass

        Collection<XMLName> getTagNamesForClass(String className)
        Uses the manifest information to find all the MXML tags that map to a specified fully-qualified ActionScript classname, such as as "spark.controls.Button"
        Parameters:
        className - Fully-qualified ActionScript classname, such as as "spark.controls.Button"
        Returns:
        A collection of XMLName's representing a MXML tags, such as a "Button" tag in the namespace "library://ns.adobe.com/flex/spark".

      • getQualifiedNamesForNamespaces

        Collection<String> getQualifiedNamesForNamespaces(Set<String> namespaceURIs,
                                                boolean manifestEntriesOnly)
        Find all the qualified names in the manifest information that have a corresponding MXML tag whose namespace is in the specified set of namespaces.
        Parameters:
        namespaceURIs - Set set of MXML tag namespace URIs such as: "library://ns.adobe.com/flex/spark"
        manifestEntriesOnly - determines if all the qualified names are returned or if only the entries from manifest files are returned.
        Returns:
        A collection of qualified names ( spark.components.Button for example ) that have correponding MXML tags in the manifest information whose namespaces are in the specified set of namespaces.
